David Miscavige , the leader of the Church of Scientology , allegedly had his apostate father followed for 18 months for fear he might reveal damaging information about the inner workings of the church .
According to police records obtained the church paid a father-son team of detectives $ 10,000 a week to track Ron Miscige 's every move , review his conversations .
The claims come just weeks after the premiere of the explosive HBO documentary Going Clear .